elf who are pulling your load as well as their own don't have to listen to your morale-sapping nonsense. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=projectorion>projectorion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Nuclear Renaissance Man</span><br>  Posts: 2816<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/6/03 8:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=322.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/2001/05/images/021011_nuclear.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/Bart-term.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: anti-US</span><hr size=1> Lets keep it friendly. I'm no big fan of US imperialism either but I can see that whoever does take space will have complete control over the Earth. The prospect of the US gaining that control frightens me but the alternative is terrifying. If it isn't the US then who will it be? Obviously, I would like to see Australia become the new global power but that just isn't going to happen. If I had to choose a new Empire from those with the means to pull it off then I guess it would have to be the US. The prospect of China having total power over us is chilling. Russia might be ok but I think the US is more likely to pull it off anyway. They have the technology. Some people would be thinking why should anybody have such power. Why can't we just outlaw space access? Thats just silly and without somebody calling the shots its only a matter of time before we all kill ourselves with nukes. Wouldn't it be nice if the UN led such a space effort. That would give us an international body with teeth which can step in and punish any nation with impugnity. Anybody launches a first strike and their country disapears under a big space rock. Problem is that it can never happen. The UN is not concerned with space exploration. They will always be a paper tiger.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zentrander>Zentrander</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>NERVA Spaceplane Pilot</span><br>  Posts: 105<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/6/03 8:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=322.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/Bart-term.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: anti-US</span><hr size=1> one government, one government!  seriously, a federation type government unifying all earth would be great. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=discovery1@nuclearspace>Discovery 1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>NERVA Spaceplane Pilot</span><br>  Posts: 216<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/6/03 9:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=322.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/Bart-term.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: anti-US</span><hr size=1> I like the idea of one government, except I fear that it would be a European style socialist democracy. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=projectorion>projectorion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Nuclear Renaissance Man</span><br>  Posts: 2827<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/7/03 3:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=322.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/2001/05/images/021011_nuclear.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/Bart-term.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: anti-US</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.nmnh.si.edu/paleo/blast_images/asteroid.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
