ate us but tolerates us because they need us economically.  Anyhow, if China wants to really show us up in space it should demonstrate how to reap the economic benefits that exist there.  Just sending people on joyrides in the fashion that we've already been doing in the last 40 years isn't going to impress anyone and I don't think China has the technology to get far beyond that.  Of course I could be wrong but I'm not holding my breath.     <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hamster@nuclearspace>Hamster</A> at: 1/7/03 5:03:38 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zentrander>Zentrander</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>NERVA Spaceplane Pilot</span><br>  Posts: 114<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/7/03 5:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=322.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/Bart-term.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: anti-US</span><hr size=1> peoples daily online is a party paper.  everything is government regulated there.  anybody who opposes the government gets very unpleasant treatment.  watch and see what people say when free press comes out.<br>
