e nuclear war. I'd rather take my chances with a new global power than nuclear war. It's a tough choice though. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zac@nuclearspace>Zac</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Space Tourist</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/11/03 1:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=322.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/Bart-term.gif" align=absmiddle>  inertia weapon?</span><hr size=1> What the heck is an inertia weapon?  From what I'm gathering it sounds like it involves taking an asteroid and smashing it into a target, or causing some sort of Tunguska like explosion over the target? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hamster@nuclearspace>Hamster</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 689<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/11/03 3:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=322.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://image1ex.villagephotos.com/extern/935754.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/Bart-term.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: inertia weapon?</span><hr size=1> An interia weapon basically uses its kinetic energy to cause damage by transferring energy from itself to the environs.  You basically got it right when you said directing asteroids at Earth would be a form of an intertial weapon. <p></p><